Reports have emerged of a break-in at the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks) head office in Silverton, Pretoria, early this morning.According to eNCA on Twitter, the Hawks have confirmed the break-in.EWN tweeted the Hawks confirmed computers were stolen during the robbery and that the incident was concentrated in the support divisions such as human resources, finance and supply chains.A team has been assembled to investigate the break-in, and the damage is still being assessed, according to EWN.BREAKING NEWS: #Hawks confirms break-in at head office in #Silverton early this morning. pic.twitter.com/QFd8hSlBOg&mdash; eNCA (@eNCA) July 5, 2017BREAKING The Hawks have confirmed to EWN that there was a break-in at their head office in Silverton early this morning.&mdash; Mandy Wiener (@MandyWiener) July 5, 2017BREAKING The Hawks have confirmed to EWN that there was a break-in at their head office in Silverton early this morning.&mdash; EWN Reporter (@ewnreporter) July 5, 2017#Hawks confirm computers were stolen in a the burglary. Incident was concentrated in the support environment (HR, Finance, Supply chain).&mdash; EWN Reporter (@ewnreporter) July 5, 2017#Hawks A team has been assembled to investigate. They are still assessing the damage but can confirm computers stolen.&mdash; EWN Reporter (@ewnreporter) July 5, 2017 Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za